TOWN CRIERS:

Darkwind's town crier system allows the addition of both general and
domain-specific messages that can be queried and announced via various
means. The messages can be advertisements for areas, quests, specific
events, and the like.

Relevant commands:

Read the help for the following commands:
criermsgs, crieradd, crieraddtimed, crierremove


Town Crier Inheritable:

There is a generic town crier inheritable (TOWN_CRIER) that will
automatically shout a variety of messages, preferring general domain
messages and messages from its own domain (set with set_domain()).
It recognizes souvrael, darkwind, kerei, hyperborea, and underworld
as domains. There is an example at /domains/darkwind/roads/obj/crier.c
that uses this inheritable.

void set_domain(string domain): 
Sets the message domain that the crier will prefer when shouting messages.

void set_all_domains(int flag):
If 1, the crier will select messages from all domains. If 0, the crier will
shout only messages only from its specified set_domain() domain and from
general messages.

void set_crier_message(string msg):
Sets the message the crier will prepend to its shouts. Defaults to "Hear ye,
hear ye!".


To add an announcement programmatically:

CRIER_D->add_announcment(string key, string msg, string domain, int minutes);

Domain is optional, and defaults to "all". The key needs to be unique
*across all the announcements*! A good key would be something like
"malraux.newbie.ad". A bad key would be something like "message".

Do not put newlines or double quotes in your messages.

You can add an announcement as many times as you want. Successive
additions of the same key merely replace. Announcements are saved,
so you only need to add the message once. The announcement will
stay until you remove it explicitly.

The "minutes" parameter will put a timeout of that many minutes on the 
announcement, after which it will automatically be removed.


To remove an announcement: 

CRIER_D->remove_announcement(string key);


To query a random announcement by domain:

CRIER_D->query_random_announcement(string domain);

Domain is optional; default is "all".

Valid domains are:

darkwind, hyperborea, souvrael, kerei, underworld, all

Of course, you can create your own domains for internal use, but
they announcements will never be queried anywhere else.


/inherits/towncrier.c is an example of a way to use the CRIER_D.
